            "text": "Oggie! Oggie! Oggie!  Oi! Oi! Oi!\nYup - had to order the Oggie - the basic steak and potatoes (with onion and rutabaga) pastie.  This tasted like growing up in the midwest in the 60s/70s - salt, pepper, beef, potatoes, onions, and some 'exotic' red wine gravy.  Nice bit of time travel during  lunch.  This was a hearty meal, and I enjoyed it.\n\nThe restaurant is cool looking - lots of trestle tables where you can sit with a big group of friends, or join some not-yet-friends who are already there.  Indoor/outdoor bar (wrong time of year for the outdoor part, but good to bear in mind for when the weather gets back to perfect).",
