            "text": "So I'm sure they're tired of being compared to Hot Pockets, but the best explanation I can come up with is gourmet hot pockets at their best. The food is absolutely killer here; I've tried four of the pasty's (pronounced liked nasty with a \"p\" not like tasty with a \"p\"-well at least that's what I've gathered from listening to the staff) and they've all been amazing. The best part is it isn't only the traditional meat cheese and potatoes. The options are all over the place and you can even bring your vegan friends. You can get a beer from the other side of the pond and the ambiance definitely feels like a good pub from across the Atlantic. \nThe only reason they aren't getting five stars is because my most recent visit; the bartender eating his dinner at the bar was clearly more important than my dinner. It's ok; it's not like with a hot meal I'd like to chase it down with a beverage of sort. The kitchen guys have always been extremely helpful and I appreciate them. The food is amazing enough and diverse enough to where I'll be back frequently, just hopefully not during my bartender's dinner time.",
