            "text": "The pasties are amazing. My two favorite are the Mexican and the Pilgrim. The Mexican has amazing flavor from hatch chilies, steak, potatoes, and egg with fresh salsa and sour cream. It's like the best breakfast burrito you've every had because that buttery flaky pasty crust can't be beat. The Pilgrim on the other hand is like that delicious meal you make the day after Thanksgiving with all the leftovers. It has turkey, stuffing, and sweet potatoes. It's delicious by itself but with the wine gravy and cranberry sauce it's become out of this world! It's like what a chicken pot pie wishes it could be and you'll be thinking about that wine gravy sauce at Thanksgiving wishing you had some. \n\nLastly, for dessert, and no meal at Cornish Pasty Co. can be complete without it, the chocolate bread pudding. Now you may be saying \"But Connor, I've had bread pudding and I don't like it.\" That's fine. It's literally like no other bread pudding. For starters I'm fairly certain the \"bread\" they use is cake. Secondly it's not cooked into a complete mush or gel. The layers of delicious sweet cake are clearly evident when you get it. About four layers on each one typed with creme anglaise and ice cream. Each bite is incredible.",
