            "text": "This locale has a menu full of Cornish pasty choices. They are a pastry with savory fillings, sort of like a hand held pot pie-comfort food to the max!! They also have a nice beer selection featuring many local brews. Started off with fresh chips and added melted cheese. They were fresh cut fries and really worth the calories!! \n\nWe ordered the cheese and onion and the Greek chicken pasty. The crust was so delicious, amaze balls really! The cheese and onion pasty was filled with potato, turnip, onion and cheese. Very tasty and satisfying (a tad salty though). Washed it down with Koffee Kolsch ale from Huss brewing company (local to Tempe AZ). This was a spectacular golden beer with a coffee and vanilla finish. \n\nThis is a great casual place with a unique food offering that I haven't seen stateside in all my travels. Small indoor bar with about 5 tables plus additional outdoor bar and seating.",
