            "text": "I have heard great things about this place just located in the downtown Tempe area. I do appreciate how the lighting is nice and dim that fits with the ambiance of the food and drinks provided. I have never really understood the menu specialties, and it was simply put as a calzone style of meals. With that I went with the meatball pastie, that included fresh sliced meatballs, basil, fresh marinara and mozzarella. This pastie is one of many that they offer depending on your cravings. \nNext time I will make an effort to try out the other Pasties and the wonderful flavors to expect !",
