            "text": "Traveling through and found this place; wish we lived here so we could go all the time. Great drink menu, dark ambiance (as many Irish pubs are), great, friendly service and amazing food. We let our waitress pick our appetizer (Scotch eggs) and our meals. She brought 2 pasty's cut  in half so we could share. Mine had turkey and sweet potatoes and my husband had beef with blue cheese (many other things inside too but these are the identifying characteristics). Scrumptious is the best word for all of it.  Everything on the menu sounded like.something we would want. We couldn't decide and that's why we let the waitress pick. She couldn't go wrong. And... Everything was so reasonably priced.  \nThis has inspired us to look for a good similar pub at home. This is a must visit place.",
