            "text": "I loved this place.  We sat at the counter and it was fascinating to watch the staff navigate the area they have for cooking, serving, prepping and dishwashing.  My vegetarian tikka masala pasty was delicious but too much to eat in one meal, so I have a great lunch for tomorrow.  My husband had the chicken pot pie pasty but wished he'd tried something a little more daring.  This place had a sense of bonhomie that owes more than a little to the tight quarters and the fun, friendly staff.  We'll be back!",
