            "text": "This place is dangerous!  It is within walking/stumbling distance of my house and offers car bombs for $3 all day, everyday.  Cornish is usually my default drink stop or eatery when I can't figure out what to eat.\nMenu is very robust and offers quite a few vegetarian offerings, which is very different and they are actually really good (this coming from a non-veggie).  My favorite is the non-traditional royale with cheese, but I haven't found one I don't like and I've had almost every single one.  They added some side dishes recently to accompany the pasty options and provides a bit more food than I can handle.\nThere are quite a few beer options on tap with some really decent tastes of the UK and others.  I love being able to find Boddington's on draft and they have it here in 32 oz. mugs!  Again, DANGER!",
