            "text": "The ratings are accurate - this is a 5 STAR place!\n\nI had gone to Tempe to check out a graduate program at ASU and decided to give this place a shot. I started off with an Old Speckled Hen draft (great beer selection by the way) and a Greek salad. After much deliberation on what pastry to order, I finally settled on the Peppered Steak. The flavors of the pastry were rich and the side of peppercorn brandy cream sauce was extra tasty. It was a slam dunk meal! \n\nThe service was good and the atmosphere was very friendly. It's a great place to go with a group or take a date. \n\n*Just a note - I went to the location on University that is tucked away in the back of a small strip mall. It is dark and does not have a lot of signage so it could be a little difficult for first timers to find even with a GPS.",
