            "text": "This comes close. As a frequent visitor of London I long for my Chips and Mushy peas. I love the decor of the place to begin with.  The seating could be a bit more comfortable but the lighting and the hipster feel of the place is strangely calming. The menu is massive and surprisingly includes an entirely vegetarian section as well. I usually order the Mexican which comes with choice of vegetarian beef or regular. I decided to give vegetarian a try. I was certainly surprised. We ordered an appetizer of curried potatoes and baked beans and they were amazing. Finally we finished the meal with some beers and a desert of bread pudding. My one complaint is that they still don't have mushy peas. However, this is one of the few places that I insist on taking people new to the east valley.",
