            "text": "First off, the food here is so god damn delicious it should be a crime. The pasties, chips, soup, broccoli bake - all of it is good. \n\nThe reason I'm only giving 4 stars is because of the service and seating setup. Most of my friends understand that eating here is kind of hellish and is usually to be avoided. The seating is very limited - if you're claustrophobic forget it. If you come with more than 1 (2 at the absolute most) people, forget it. There are two booth-table hybrids, way in the back, but be warned that your server will inform you that at any time, no matter how awkward, complete strangers are allowed to just plop down next to you at the same table and join your party. If you are a Larry David type individual with a need for personal space, you're gonna have a bad time. If it fits, they sits. \n\nAs far as the service goes, the soup de jour is \"I don't give a shit.\" \n\nOne time we asked for straws and our server just chucked them at us. I've asked \"do you have any seats available?\" and been told \"I don't know, go look.\" We've had employees actually ask us to move, along with all of our stuff, to a different table (yes, really) to accommodate another group. I've been given dirty looks for asking for a slice of lemon in my water. All kinds of heartwarming interactions.\n\nI haven't been to the other locations, but if you're a masochist that loves gourmet hot pockets this location is for you. Otherwise either get really drunk before you eat here, or just get it to-go.",
