            "text": "This place is the gosh darned bomb.  The food here is so crazy good I can't even begin to describe it.  To boot, they have Strongbow cider on tap, happy hour daily from  3 to 6, and the most unbelievable pasties we've had outside of Truro, Cornwall.  And that's not even mentioning the Shirley Temple pudding.....The food is rib-sticking and makes you feel like you are lying down on a soft couch and blanket when you eat it.  There is a type of pasty for everyone here, so don't read any more.  Just go.  In the entire valley, this is our 2nd favorite place (the first being a local pizza joint, Palermo's.)  The kids working at the place might be a bit young, brash, and stoner-looking, but the owners and recipes are faultless.  We have been here avout 20 times in the last 2 years, and every time the experience is the same.  Go.  Now.",
