            "text": "I live down the street from this spot and I have got to say its probably my favorite place to eat in AZ. My fiance and I eat there at least once a week. I have eaten every Pasty on the menu, and I honestly don't think i have been disappointed once (maybe a thing or two forgotten when we do take out but they always make up for it) \n\nIt is a super original spot to take your family if you are in town. There is a nice dining room with a bar and an outdoor patio on the north side, and then on the south end there is a whole other local bar spot called \"The Beast\". A lot of people don't even know it's there. Its a super hip dark lit bar with comfy couches and a stage area that has some old church pews as tables setup. There is a couple pool tables and dart boards. They have live music sometimes and serve the whole Cornish menu. Its pretty much just another part of the same restaurant, but for us locals. A part of the kitchen is behind the bar and you can see how much preparation and fresh ingredients go into these pasties. \n\nCheck out their spot on Mill Ave. also for a shot and a late night snack. They usually have the whole menu available as well. Love this restaurant like I love New York pizza. And thats a lot!!",
