            "text": "Had lunch plans for a buddy and I since he was going to be in the area for business and he'd never been to Cornish Pasty so we headed on over...\n\nThis is the first time that I've been to the Tempe version of this place... I've actually gone to the Mesa version quite a few times... and while this place is good it's not as good as the Mesa version.\n\nParking was a little rough as the lot was pretty full for lunch... I can't imagine this place on a Friday or Saturday night.\n\nPasty's in general are really good... and this time I got the Carne Adovada which was highly recommended by the server and some patrons next to us... it wasn't that great for me though for whatever reason.\n\nThe english pub vibe is great and the beer selection is awesome as well... I'd come back... but if I have a choice, I'd head to the Mesa location over the Tempe one.",
