            "text": "I love love love love this place. I wish the one in downtown Phoenix was open, but driving all the way to Tempe is worth it for Cornish Pasty. The best thing about the food is that it's not just one type of cuisine you're stuck with. There are options that are Italian, Mexican, Indian, British, and others so you have the option to try something new each visit. I'm also thankful that they have so many vegetarian choices, seeing how I've noticed that many restaurants in the Valley rely way too much on meat products. The atmosphere is also pretty cool too, there's no obnoxious fluorescent lighting or anything and it is pretty intimate (in a good way) as well as the fact that there's always great music playing thanks to the employees. Extra points for having a full bar :)",
