            "text": "Okay, before I get into praising this place as a go-to spot for anyone within a 30 minute driving radius, a couple peculiarities about this place:\n1.  The ambiance is dark and pub-like. No getting around that. If that works for you, cool; most parents with little kids, however, will feel out of place, and not because of anything wrong.  I came here with my newborn and 3-year-old after the zoo, it felt awkward but was worth it for the food and beer.  If you come when it's comfortable outside, then you can sit outside and not be in the dark.\n2.  It's easier to see this place from Hardy Drive than from University Drive.\n\nOk now that's out of the way. The British pub ambiance here perfectly matches the food and beer. Great curated beer list, and the pasties are awesome. The bean dip starter had an interesting vinegar flavor, and came with great crackers (they were softer than normal crackers and I'm pretty sure house-made). The bread that came alongside the soup was definitely house-made and had gravitas. It was great!\nWhen I ordered my Rosemary chicken pasty, my server recommended a brown ale. It went great with my meal!   The crust was perfectly dense and flaky, and the insides breathed Rosemary while all the chicken and other vegetable flavors supported each other while sitting in a delicious sauce.  My mother in law is a vegetarian, so she ordered the onion and cheese, which I tasted and was FANTASTIC.  Service was really good and friendly throughout, and the food and beer support the time-travel and country-transporting effect that the ambiance offers. Definitely a go-to dining experience, even if you don't drink beer.",
