            "text": "The food is amazing! The ambience is unique. The service is...friendly.\n\nLiterally for a year or two, I had a friend telling me to come to Cornish Pasty Company. He made it a point to visit this place every time he came into town, and he felt strongly that I should do the same. Now that I'm actually living in town, I made this happen. And I must say, I'm sad it took me this long to get there, because I've been missing out!\n\nFirst off, a pasty is a wonderful, flaky pocket of deliciousness. It's like the best pot pie crust wrapped completely around a variety of different combinations. The crust alone is fantastic, and when you put those fillings in it, I couldn't get enough.\n\nWhen I walked into this place, I kind of wondered where I had gotten myself. The Tempe location is nearly pitch black inside. On a positive note, it's a nice place to go in the middle of the hot summer here, because it was nice and cool inside. There's also a nice porch to eat outside if the weather permits. Seating is on a \"help yourself\" basis, and I think this may lend itself towards the servers not necessarily noticing you immediately. That's what happened to us, both at the beginning and the end of our meal.\n\nI had the Pilgrim pasty, which is essentially a Thanksgiving meal all wrapped inside a pastyl. It has turkey, grilled onions, sweet potatoes, chicken, and stuffing, and is served with a red wine gravy and cranberry sauce. I'm a sucker for cranberry sauce and for Thanksgiving in general, and this totally hit the spot! Normally I'd have been in a bit of a spot trying to decide among the various delicious-sounding options, but when I saw this one, I knew I had to have it. One of my friends had the Meat and Cheese pasty, and it was solid as well.\n\nI just looked at the menu again as I was writing this, and my mouth is watering now. There are so many other great selections, and I'm eager to get back and try more.\n\nIn summary, great food and unique atmosphere, but don't be in a rush, because the service isn't all that speedy.",
