            "text": "This was my second time in Phoenix and since we were staying around the Tempe area I could not let the opportunity pass us by of not trying the most Yelped place in all of Phoenix! I've never had a pasty before so I didn't know what to expect but judging from the pictures I had a general idea of what it would taste it. We came in fairly late around 10pm and since I was going to run the Arizona 1/2 marathon the following morning I opted for one of the lighter dishes. They truly have a wide variety of what would go in your pasty from burger, to Alfredo to even Indian chicken tikka masala. I ordered the salmon one, which I did enjoy. The crust went perfectly with the well cooked salmon. There was also spinach with dill sauce and other things that I can't remember. If I was feeling adventurous and didn't have to worry about eating light I would of ordered the Chicken Tikka Masala since our server said that was one of her favorites. Although we had no room for dessert we ordered a banoffee pie to go. This was really tasty as well great combination of bananas, gram cracker, whipped cream and caramel. From that Yelp picture the caption says it's Banana Cream pie, don't make the mistake of asking for it because our server corrected us and told us it was Banofee pie, haha! The inside of this place is a hybrid between a dive and a pub because it was dark and had community style tables. Our server was pretty good I guess but nothing memorable in terms of outstanding customer service. I can see why this is a popular spot among ASU students. Most if not all the pasty selections are less than $10. Even half a pasty is filling so you could even share one. Pasty places aren't too popular so I would definitely recommend trying them out. I don't know when I'll be in Phoenix again, but if I'm in the Tempe area I will definitely stop by.",
