            "text": "Probably one of the best English foods I have ever had. Their pasties definitely pack in the flavors, not very well known for English food. I would highly recommend The Royal with Cheese. It's sort of their twist of a hamburger and fries stuffed in a calzone. The servers are very friendly and welcoming. Give this place a try, you are in for a pleasant surprise :)\n\nThe only issue I have is how long it take to make one once you have ordered. I would suggest to call ahead and order before eating there. I can understand the high price for just one pasty (around $9 per pastey not including a side) because they make each one by hand with fresh ingredients. The restaurant can work on the interior design as its a bit confusing, a mix between modern and old style English pub. Not a big fan of the church pews for seats because its hard to sit upright while eating. Its just awkward. If you can look past the odd decor, this place in not at all that bad.",
