            "text": "We were in Phoenix unexpectedly for one night and needed a place close to our hotel to catch up with friends.  Based on Yelp recommendations tried Cornish Pasty.\n\nThankfully, we were able to sit outside where the noise level was much less than inside.  If you want to visit, don't come here on Friday night and sit inside!  Restaurant hard to find as there are no signs and windows covered in black curtains.\n\nPasties were excellent!  Didn't love the red gravy, but it was ok.  Had appetizers and salad and dessert, all very good and vegan or vegetarian friendly.  The chips (french fries) were delicious, although a smallish portion.  Four of us easily shared a full size garden salad.  I have not had a pavlova since visiting New Zealand 20 years ago and would come here just for that, it was fantastic.  All the desserts are huge too!\n\nWe will be back.",
