            "text": "Definitely worth a try. It's a bit of a dark dive with ample counter / bar seating in multiple rooms for prep and cooking views. Check out the back bar with pool table action or outdoor patio at other end of the strip mall. :). \n\nNice (albeit limited) cocktail and wine menu, good draft choices and an expansive pasty menu. If you haven't tried a true Cornish pasty, that alone is reason to visit this spot; I've never seen a wider selection. The pasty is TASTY, that's for damn sure. Be prepared to wait. My Chicken Tikka Masala took more than 30 mins. But, it was rich and delicious.",
