            "text": "What a wonderful place to to have dinner and share stories with friends.  Let me tell you this place was jammed packed with all the tables filled and the noise level was loud, but you can still carry on a conversation. Okay enough about my time here lets get to the food. WOW is all I can say.  I felt like I was in a English pub.  Huge beer and wine list.  There are so many combination of pasties that's the hardest part was making a decision on which one I wanted.  My husband got the Greek chicken which he gobbled up and I got the Oggie.  The Oggie is fulled with steak, potatoes and other veggies, it was so delicious! I could only eat half.  the pasty crust was light and just melted in you mouth. Okay so here is the deal  My husband had 2 beers I had a cocktail, together we had two pasties and a side order of home made chips and our bill was $35.00 without  tip.  I have been to restaurants in the valley where $35.00 is just for the entree.  Yes Yes Yes we are going to go back.  I want to buy some $7.50 each to cook at home.",
