            "text": "Ok I tried this place from recommendations from Yelp and they were all true. I had layovers for 3 nights in a row and ate here 3 times! It is so good I want to try everything on the menu! All the ingredients are so fresh and the meat is so tender and beautifully seasoned! But the Dough is to die for. Baked to a perfect golden brown crispy melt-in-your- mouth goodness. Today I was craving another pasty but was too far from Mill Ave to go back but discovered the other location on University and got a roast beef for lunch and 2half baked pasties to go so I can enjoy them at home. Don't miss this place. The two locations in Tempe look like great places for craft beer but can't attest to that as I was going to work and could not imbibe, but both locations have seating and have a very laid back feel. I am telling all who will listen to try this place. I will be in Vegas in two weeks and will seek out their location there!",
