            "text": "My first time to this place that we stumbled on and oh my gosh, heaven! When we first entered into the restaurant in the middle of the day - It was very dark. I thought we were going to bar to drink some irish beers and I was about to turn around and go back out to see if this was the right place but, the chef immediately greeted us as if he knew \"Hi, come in - have a seat anywhere!\" The restaurant looks like a bar you could have fun during Happy Hour with friends after work - needed cold beers - YES!\nBut, because it was during the work week and mid-day, we really wanted to try their cornish pastry dish. I'm so boring I stuck with the original \"Shepard's pie\" and my husband/I shared the Sticky Toffee Pudding. Absolutely, delicious. The Pastis (Pastry) was just so warm, flaky, buttery tasting, and just melts in your mouth after each bite. I probably could just eat the pastry all by itself - it's so good. The meal entree, I think it was a huge size for one person to eat but, as the history goes it was for feeding the miners, Lol! I didn't think I would be able to finish my entree but, surprisingly I did. I was super stuffed though but, my kane (husband) wanted dessert - so crazy! So we shared the toffee pudding - ohhh so glad we did. The toffee cake came in a  cute little cast iron bowl with melted toffee all over and nice vanilla ice cream on the side - we both ate it so fast, we didn't even blink and puff - was gone! \nOur waitress was so nice and kept coming back to check in on us, filling up our waters, seeing how we were doing, and being amazing! Can't wait to go back again...Yummmy, I'm hungry already just writing about it! LoL",
