            "text": "If you want some hearty meat and carbs, come and get some delicious pasties, which are what they're famous for! I kid you not their tandoori wings and cheese broccoli were also surprisingly delicious!\n\nFood-wise, great. I tried their shepherd's pie pasty and it was just so savory and flavorful. We completely devoured the perfectly seasoned and grilled tandoori chicken wings. The cheese broccoli was just another way to ramp up our fat and calorie intake without any regrets.\n\nLove the vibe there. People were all chilling and staff were friendly. It was kind of confusing at first. It was not easy to find, being tucked in the corner at the back with no bright signs or large entrance. We managed to locate this restaurant. When we walked in, we didn't know who the host/ess was, so we had to wait at the entrance to see if anyone would come and greet us. Finally a waitress walked to us and seat us at a picnic table outside. There were at least two large community tables out there, and people, probably mostly students, were just hanging out, drinking, eating and having fun. It's just a very relaxing way to spend the night.\n\nGreat place to eat and hang out! Prices were pretty reasonable too.",
